<div class="dcf-wrapper">
  <div class="header">
    <div class="header-content">
      <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
      <h1>3M (MMM)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of 3M Company. Using real-time financial data, disclosed assumptions, and mathematical rigor.</p>
      <p class="date">Data retrieved live · Using TTM/Annual financials</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
    <div class="verdict-card">
      <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
      <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
      <div class="verdict-vs">vs. current price of {safeCurrentPrice > 0 ? `$${safeCurrentPrice.toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
      <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
        {verdictText}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{formatBillions(revenueTTM)}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Revenue (TTM)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{formatBillions(ocfTTM)}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Operating Cash Flow</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{epsTTM !== null ? `$${epsTTM.toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{opMarginTTM}%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{formatBillions(netCash)}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Net Cash / (Debt)</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
    <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
    <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model to calculate the intrinsic value of 3M. This approach values a company based on the present value of its future cash flows.</p>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">1</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Determine Base Cash Flow</h4>
        <p>3M's Free Cash Flow has been heavily impacted by massive legal settlements (Combat Arms Earplugs, PFAS water contamination). To avoid penalizing the core business's ongoing cash generation capability with one-time or structured legal payouts that are already largely known/reserved, we explicitly use <strong>Operating Cash Flow</strong> ({formatBillions(ocfTTM)}) as the base proxy for this model, adapting for the volatility in their standard FCF.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">2</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Project cash flows (Phase 1)</h4>
        <p>We project cash flows to grow at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}% per year</strong> for the next 5 years. This reflects a modest growth expectation post-restructuring and post-Solventum spinoff, focusing on core industrial, materials, and safety segments.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">3</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
        <p>After Year 5, we assume growth stabilizes at a terminal rate of <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong>. This is lower than long-term historical GDP, appropriate for a mature, slower-growth industrial conglomerate.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">4</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Discount to Present Value</h4>
        <p>We discount these future cash flows back to today using a <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</strong> discount rate. This accounts for the 10Y Treasury yield (4.18%) plus a risk premium, adjusted slightly higher for 3M's debt load and residual litigation headline risks.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
    <h2>Core Assumptions</h2>

    <div class="assumption-grid">
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
        <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          Conservative outlook. 3M has historically struggled to achieve high single-digit top-line growth. Post-Solventum spin-off and after settling major litigation, a {(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}% CAGR reflects stabilization and optimization rather than aggressive expansion.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
        <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          10Y Treasury is ~4.18%. With a standard equity risk premium and considering 3M's substantial debt ({formatBillions(totalDebt)}) and litigation payment obligations over the next decade, a {(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}% hurdle rate ensures a margin of safety against execution risk.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
        <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          A mature industrial company should grow roughly in line with inflation or slightly below global GDP growth. {(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% assumes 3M maintains its economic moat in materials science but does not outpace general economic expansion.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
    <h2>Projected Cash Flows (Base: Operating Cash Flow)</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
            <th>Projected CF ($M)</th>
            <th>PV Factor</th>
            <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Base (TTM/Recent)</td>
            <td>{formatCurrency(baseCashFlow)}</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>—</td>
          </tr>
          {projectedFCF.map(p => (
            <tr>
              <td>Year {p.year}</td>
              <td>{formatCurrency(p.fcf)}</td>
              <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
              <td>{formatCurrency(p.pvFCF)}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">{formatCurrency(pvPhase1)}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
    <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
            <th>Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Year 6 Cash Flow</td>
            <td>{formatCurrency(Math.round(fcfYear6))}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Terminal Value</td>
            <td>{formatCurrency(terminalValue)}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">{formatCurrency(pvTerminalValue)}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
    <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
            <th>Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
            <td>{formatCurrency(pvPhase1)}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
            <td>{formatCurrency(pvTerminalValue)}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>= Enterprise Value</td>
            <td>{formatCurrency(enterpriseValue)}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>+ Net Cash (Cash − Debt)</td>
            <td>{formatCurrency(netCash)}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>= Equity Value</td>
            <td>{formatCurrency(equityValue)}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>÷ Shares Outstanding</td>
            <td>{sharesOutstanding > 0 ? sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString() : 'N/A'}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td>Intrinsic Value Per Share</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ HISTORICAL CHARTS ═══ -->
    <h2>5-Year Financial History</h2>
    <p>A look at 3M's historical performance, illustrating the impact of spin-offs, restructurings, and litigation settlements.</p>

    <h3>Revenue ($B)</h3>
    <div class="bar-chart">
      {revenueHistory.map(r => (
        <div class="bar-row">
          <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
          <div class="bar-track">
            {r.value !== null ? (
              <div class="bar-fill revenue" style={`width: ${(Math.abs(r.value) / maxRev) * 100}%`}>
                ${(r.value / 1000).toFixed(2)}B
              </div>
            ) : (
              <span style="font-size:0.8rem; padding-left:12px; color:#5a6a80;">N/A</span>
            )}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h3>Free Cash Flow ($B)</h3>
    <div class="bar-chart">
      {fcfHistory.map(r => (
        <div class="bar-row">
          <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
          <div class="bar-track">
            {r.value !== null ? (
              <div class={`bar-fill ${r.value < 0 ? 'negative' : 'fcf'}`} style={`width: ${(Math.abs(r.value) / maxFcf) * 100}%`}>
                ${(r.value / 1000).toFixed(2)}B
              </div>
            ) : (
              <span style="font-size:0.8rem; padding-left:12px; color:#5a6a80;">N/A</span>
            )}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h3>Earnings Per Share (Diluted)</h3>
    <div class="bar-chart">
      {epsHistoryChart.map(r => (
        <div class="bar-row">
          <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
          <div class="bar-track">
            {r.value !== null ? (
               <div class={`bar-fill ${r.value < 0 ? 'negative' : 'eps'}`} style={`width: ${(Math.abs(r.value) / maxEps) * 100}%`}>
                ${r.value.toFixed(2)}
              </div>
            ) : (
              <span style="font-size:0.8rem; padding-left:12px; color:#5a6a80;">N/A</span>
            )}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS ═══ -->
    <h2>Sensitivity Analysis</h2>
    <p>Intrinsic value changes dramatically based on your assumptions. Find the intersection of the discount rate and growth rate you believe is most accurate for 3M.</p>

    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table class="sensitivity-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Discount Rate ↓ / Growth →</th>
            {sensitivityGrowth.map(g => (
              <th class={g === growthRatePhase1 ? 'current' : ''}>{(g * 100).toFixed(0)}%</th>
            ))}
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {sensitivityTable.map(row => (
            <tr>
              <td>{(row.dr * 100).toFixed(0)}%</td>
              {row.values.map((v, i) => (
                <td class={row.dr === discountRate && sensitivityGrowth[i] === growthRatePhase1 ? 'current' : ''}>
                  ${v}
                </td>
              ))}
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ RISKS ═══ -->
    <h2>Key Risks & Considerations</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Litigation Payments:</strong> 3M has agreed to pay billions over the next decade for the Combat Arms Earplugs ($6B) and PFAS public water systems ($10.3B) settlements. While structured, these will act as a significant drag on actual free cash flow available to shareholders.</li>
      <li><strong>Solventum Spin-off:</strong> The spin-off of its healthcare unit (Solventum) removed a historically stable, higher-margin revenue stream. 3M is now more exposed to cyclical industrial end-markets.</li>
      <li><strong>Dividend Cut:</strong> Following the Solventum spin-off, 3M reset its dividend payout to reflect the new, smaller company structure, breaking its decades-long streak as a Dividend Aristocrat. This changes the investor base profile.</li>
      <li><strong>Macroeconomic Sensitivity:</strong> As an industrial conglomerate, 3M's revenue is highly sensitive to global manufacturing output, consumer electronics demand, and automotive production.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>Why use Operating Cash Flow instead of Free Cash Flow?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">3M's reported Free Cash Flow has been heavily depressed and volatile due to massive, one-time (though structured) legal settlements. Using depressed FCF would severely undervalue the core operations. We substitute Operating Cash Flow to estimate the fundamental cash generation power of the business, though investors must mentally account for the billions that will be paid out in settlements.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Are the legal settlements fully accounted for?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">The settlement liabilities are largely booked on the balance sheet, which is reflected in the Total Debt and Net Cash figures. By subtracting Net Debt from Enterprise Value, the model implicitly deducts the present value of these recorded obligations.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Why a 9% discount rate?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">A 9% required rate of return reflects the 10-year treasury yield (~4.18%) plus an equity risk premium, adjusted upward for 3M's elevated debt levels and residual business risks post-restructuring.</div>
      </details>
    </div>

